{"action":"opened","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/46659","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/46659/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/46659/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/46659/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/46659","id":1364128529,"node_id":"I_kwDOABkWpM5RTvMR","number":46659,"title":"Embargo for new version docs","user":{"login":"mortenpi","id":147757,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0Nzc1Nw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/147757?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi","html_url":"https://github.com/mortenpi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mortenpi/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":229907793,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyMjk5MDc3OTM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/docsystem","name":"docsystem","color":"d4c5f9","default":false,"description":"The documentation building system"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2022-09-07T05:55:28Z","updated_at":"2022-09-07T05:55:28Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Right now, when a new version gets tagged, we immediately deploy the docs and make them available to the users (e.g. under the `v1/` URL), even before the release is officially announced. This means that for a while, users are accessing docs for a future version of Julia (especially noticeable for minor releases) and it also leads to the link to the PDF not working (since it gets deployed later; although this would be mitigated by https://github.com/JuliaCI/julia-buildkite/issues/198).

Having the docs on `gh-pages` early is not actually a problem as long as we hold off on updating the symlinks and `versioninfo.js`. So what we could do is have a small file sitting on the [`gh-pages` branch](https://github.com/JuliaLang/docs.julialang.org/tree/gh-pages) that declares an embargo on a particular version of the docs, and make sure that `doc/make.jl` doesn't generate the symlinks for that. Once a release is fully out, that file would then have to be manually removed/updated, to remove the embargo.

